Detailed Description

Settings for a map.

The settings include what to draw and how to draw it.

Member Enumeration Documentation

enum MapSettings::ShowType
 

Types to be shown in the final gfx map.

Enumeration values:
MAP  Map items.
TOPOGRAPH_MAP  Topographical information.
POI  Point of Interest items.
ROUTE  Routes.
TRAFFIC  Traffic information POIs.
CITY_CENTRE  City centres.
SCALE  Whether or not to draw scale.
EVENT  Event POIs.

void MapSettings::addSettingFor (  GfxFeature::gfxFeatureType  featureType,
uint32  highScaleLevel,
uint32  lowScaleLevel,
bool  onMap,
bool  borderOnMap,
bool  textOnMap = false,
DrawSettings::drawstyle_t  drawStyle = DrawSettings::LINE,
DrawSettings::symbol_t  drawSymbol = DrawSettings::SQUARE_3D_SYMBOL,
int  lineWidth = 1,
GDUtils::Color::CoolColor  drawColor = static_cast< GDUtils::Color::CoolColor >(0x000000),
int  borderLineWidth = 1,
GDUtils::Color::CoolColor  borderColor = static_cast< GDUtils::Color::CoolColor >(0x000000),
int  fontSize = 10,
GDUtils::Color::CoolColor  fontColor = static_cast< GDUtils::Color::CoolColor >(0x000000),
const char *  fontName = "Vera.ttf",
bool  copyString = false
) 
 

Setting for a GfxFeatureType.

Note that most default values really do NOT make any sense to use, except if the settings is for a feature that should not present on the map.

Parameters:
featureType The type of feature to set MapSettings for.
highScaleLevel The highest scaleLevel the setting is for.
lowScaleLevel The lowest scaleLevel the setting is for.
onMap If featuretype should be on map.
borderOnMap If featuretypes border should be on map.
textOnMap If featuretypes text should be on map.
drawStyle Type of drawing, filled, line etc..
drawSymbol If drawStyle if symbol then this indicates which symbol.
lineWidth Linewidth in pixels. drawColor Color of the line.
fontSize The fonts size for this featureType.
fontName Name of the font to use.
copyString If string should be copied, default false.
